  "notes": "Fijian (Na Vosa Vakaviti), Oceanic (Central Pacific) language of Fiji. The Latin orthography devised by David Cargill (1830s) is phonemic but assigns unusual values to several letters: ⟨b d q⟩ are the prenasalised stops /ᵐb ⁿd ᵑɡ/, ⟨g⟩ is /ŋ/, ⟨c⟩ is /ð/ and ⟨v⟩ is /β/. /p/ and /f/ occur only in loanwords. Vowel length is phonemic and written with a macron; the macronned vowels are not enumerated separately here. Fiji Hindi is written in Devanagari and is a different language.",
